WEBVTT

00:17.860 --> 00:22.020
CHAPTER XIII. ANOTHER VIEW OF HESTER

00:23.700 --> 00:32.400
In her late, singular interview with Mr Dimmesdale, Hester Prynne was shocked at the condition to which she found the clergyman reduced.

00:33.220 --> 00:40.300
His nerve seemed absolutely destroyed. His moral force was abased into more than childish weakness.

00:40.820 --> 00:47.440
It grovelled helpless on the ground, even while his intellectual faculties retained their pristine strength,

00:47.440 --> 00:53.160
or had perhaps acquired a morbid energy which disease alone could have given them.

00:53.800 --> 01:02.940
With her knowledge of a train of circumstances hidden from all others, she could readily infer that besides the legitimate action of his own conscience,

01:03.520 --> 01:11.560
a terrible machinery had been brought to bear and was still operating on Mr Dimmesdale's well-being and repose.

01:11.560 --> 01:20.740
Knowing what this poor fallen man had once been, her whole soul was moved by the shuddering terror with which she had appealed to her,

01:20.820 --> 01:26.080
the outcast woman, for support against his instinctively discovered enemy.

01:27.020 --> 01:31.560
She decided, moreover, that he had a right to her utmost aid.

01:32.540 --> 01:41.200
Little accustomed in her long seclusion from society to measure her ideas of right and wrong by any standard external to herself,

01:41.200 --> 01:48.380
Esther saw, or seemed to see, that there lay a responsibility upon her in reference to the clergyman,

01:48.760 --> 01:52.340
which she owed to no other, nor to the whole world besides.

01:53.080 --> 02:01.820
The links that united her to the rest of humankind, links of flowers or silk or gold or whatever the material, had all been broken.

02:02.720 --> 02:08.400
Here was the iron link of mutual crime which neither he nor she could break.

02:08.400 --> 02:13.160
Like all other ties, it brought along with it its obligations.

02:14.960 --> 02:22.860
Hester Prynne did not now occupy precisely the same position in which we beheld her during the earlier periods of her ignominy.

02:23.780 --> 02:27.740
Years had come and gone. Pearl was now seven years old.

02:28.440 --> 02:37.080
Her mother, with the scarlet letter on her breast, glittering in its fantastic embroidery, had long been a familiar object to the townspeople.

02:38.020 --> 02:43.260
As is apt to be the case when a person stands out in any prominence before the community,

02:44.020 --> 02:49.460
and at the same time interferes neither with public nor individual interests and convenience,

02:50.220 --> 02:55.480
a species of general regard had ultimately grown up in reference to Hester Prynne.

02:56.160 --> 03:04.480
It is to the credit of human nature that, except where its selfishness is brought into play, it loves more readily than it hates.

03:05.120 --> 03:10.160
Hatred, by a gradual and quiet process, will even be transformed to love,

03:10.420 --> 03:16.840
unless the change be impeded by a continually new irritation of the original feeling of hostility.

03:18.080 --> 03:23.240
In this matter of Hester Prynne, there was neither irritation nor irksomeness.

03:23.860 --> 03:29.320
She never battled with the public, but submitted uncomplainingly to its worst usage.

03:29.920 --> 03:33.140
She made no claim upon it in requital for what she suffered.

03:33.140 --> 03:35.540
She did not weigh upon its sympathies.

03:37.280 --> 03:45.640
Then also the blameless purity of her life during all these years in which she had been set apart to infamy was reckoned largely in her favour.

03:46.380 --> 03:52.440
With nothing now to lose in the sight of mankind, and with no hope and seemingly no wish of gaining anything,

03:53.120 --> 03:58.740
it could only be a genuine regard for virtue that had brought back the poor wanderer to its paths.

03:58.740 --> 04:06.600
It was perceived, too, that while Hester never put forward even the humblest title to share in the world's privileges,

04:07.180 --> 04:14.300
further than to breathe the common air and earn daily bread for little Pearl and herself by the faithful labour of her hands,

04:14.860 --> 04:21.580
she was quick to acknowledge her sisterhood with the race of man whenever benefits were to be conferred.

04:21.580 --> 04:26.060
None so ready as she to give of her little substance to every demand of poverty,

04:26.560 --> 04:33.120
even though the bitter-hearted pauper threw back a jibe in requital of the food brought regularly to his door,

04:33.620 --> 04:38.380
or the garments wrought for him by the fingers that could have embroidered a monarch's robe.

04:39.920 --> 04:44.220
None so self-devoted as Hester when pestilence stalked through the town.

04:44.220 --> 04:52.800
In all seasons of calamity, indeed, whether general or of individuals, the outcast of society at once found her place.

04:53.600 --> 05:00.020
She came not as a guest, but as a rightful inmate into the household that was darkened by trouble,

05:00.560 --> 05:06.780
as if its gloomy twilight were a medium in which she was entitled to hold intercourse with her fellow-creature.

05:07.960 --> 05:12.580
There glimmered the embroidered letter, with comfort in its unearthly ray.

05:12.580 --> 05:17.120
Elsewhere the token of sin, it was the taper of the sick chamber.

05:18.160 --> 05:24.120
It had even thrown its gleam in the sufferer's hard extremity across the verge of time.

05:24.820 --> 05:29.760
It had shown him where to set his foot while the light of earth was fast becoming dim,

05:30.280 --> 05:32.740
and ere the light of futurity could reach him.

05:33.500 --> 05:37.560
In such emergencies Hester's nature showed itself warm and rich,

05:37.560 --> 05:45.060
a wellspring of human tenderness, unfailing to every real demand, and inexhaustible by the largest.

05:46.220 --> 05:51.380
Her breast, with its badge of shame, was but the softer pillow for the head that needed one.

05:52.260 --> 05:59.760
She was self-ordained a sister of mercy, or, we may rather say, the world's heavy hand had so ordained her,

05:59.980 --> 06:03.400
when neither the world nor she looked forward to this result.

06:04.200 --> 06:06.440
The letter was the symbol of her calling.

06:07.580 --> 06:12.080
Such helpfulness was found in her, so much power to do and power to sympathize,

06:13.120 --> 06:17.840
that many people refused to interpret the scarlet A by its original signification.

06:19.060 --> 06:23.640
They said it meant Abel, so strong was Hester Prynne, with a woman's strength.

06:24.320 --> 06:27.100
It was only the darkened house that could contain her.

06:27.720 --> 06:30.640
When sunshine came again, she was not there.

06:31.460 --> 06:33.760
Her shadow had faded across the threshold.

06:33.760 --> 06:40.640
The helpful inmate had departed without one backward glance to gather up the mead of gratitude,

06:41.100 --> 06:45.300
if any were in the hearts of those whom she had served so zealously.

06:46.880 --> 06:50.480
Meeting them in the street, she never raised her head to receive their greeting.

06:51.380 --> 06:56.760
If they were resolute to accost her, she laid her finger on the scarlet letter and passed on.

06:57.920 --> 07:01.260
This might be pride, but was so like humility,

07:01.820 --> 07:06.340
that it produced all the softening influence of the latter quality on the public mind.

07:07.120 --> 07:09.220
The public is despotic in its temper.

07:09.940 --> 07:15.100
It is capable of denying common justice when too strenuously demanded as a right.

07:15.920 --> 07:20.520
But quite as frequently, it awards more than justice when the appeal is made,

07:21.000 --> 07:25.000
as despots love to have it made, entirely to its generosity.

07:26.660 --> 07:30.400
Interpreting Hester Prynne's deportment as an appeal of this nature,

07:31.200 --> 07:35.440
society was inclined to show its former victim a more benign countenance

07:35.440 --> 07:39.760
than she cared to be favoured with, or perchance, than she deserved.

07:40.640 --> 07:43.840
The rulers and the wise and learned men of the community

07:43.840 --> 07:48.800
were longer in acknowledging the influence of Hester's good qualities than the people.

07:49.560 --> 07:52.640
The prejudices which they shared in common with the latter

07:52.640 --> 07:56.960
were fortified in themselves by an iron framework of reasoning

07:56.960 --> 08:00.980
that made it a far tougher labour to expel them.

08:01.940 --> 08:07.880
Day by day, nevertheless, their sour and rigid wrinkles were relaxing into something

08:07.880 --> 08:13.740
which, in the due course of years, might grow to be an expression of almost benevolence.

08:14.960 --> 08:18.380
Thus it was with the men of rank on whom their eminent position

08:18.380 --> 08:21.220
imposed the guardianship of the public morals.

08:22.820 --> 08:27.420
Individuals in private life, meanwhile, had quite forgiven Hester Prynne for her frailty.

08:28.320 --> 08:32.420
Nay more, they had begun to look upon the scarlet letter as the token,

08:32.920 --> 08:37.580
not of that one sin for which she had borne so long and dreary a penance,

08:37.980 --> 08:40.140
but of her many good deeds since.

08:40.760 --> 08:44.820
Do you see that woman with the embroidered badge, they would say to strangers?

08:45.180 --> 08:49.940
It is our Hester, the town's own Hester, who is so kind to the poor,

08:49.940 --> 08:54.180
so helpful to the sick, so comfortable to the afflicted.

08:54.840 --> 08:59.560
Then it is true the propensity of human nature to tell the very worst of itself,

09:00.100 --> 09:01.860
when embodied in the person of another,

09:02.100 --> 09:06.280
would constrain them to whisper the black scandal of bygone years.

09:07.280 --> 09:12.180
It was nonetheless a fact, however, that in the eyes of the very men who spoke thus,

09:12.660 --> 09:16.080
the scarlet letter had the effect of the cross on a nun's bosom.

09:17.520 --> 09:20.240
It imparted to the wearer a kind of sacredness,

09:20.940 --> 09:24.180
which enabled her to walk securely amid all peril.

09:25.280 --> 09:28.200
Had she fallen among thieves, it would have kept her safe.

09:29.340 --> 09:31.660
It was reported, and believed by many,

09:31.980 --> 09:34.620
that an Indian had drawn his arrow against the badge,

09:34.980 --> 09:38.560
and that the missile struck it and fell harmless to the ground.

09:40.440 --> 09:44.800
The effect of the symbol, or rather of the position in respect to society

09:44.800 --> 09:48.820
that was indicated by it, on the mind of Hester Prynne herself,

09:49.080 --> 09:50.700
was powerful and peculiar.

09:51.900 --> 09:55.060
All the light and graceful foliage of her character

09:55.060 --> 09:58.220
had been withered up by this red-hot brand,

09:58.880 --> 10:03.160
and had long ago fallen away, leaving a bare and harsh outline,

10:03.600 --> 10:05.080
which might have been repulsive,

10:05.280 --> 10:08.980
had she possessed friends or companions to be repelled by it.

10:09.600 --> 10:13.580
Even the attractiveness of her person had undergone a similar change.

10:14.200 --> 10:18.140
It might be partly owing to the studied austerity of her dress,

10:18.520 --> 10:21.260
and partly to the lack of demonstration in her manners.

10:22.200 --> 10:24.520
It was a sad transformation, too,

10:24.640 --> 10:28.420
that her rich and luxuriant hair had either been cut off,

10:28.600 --> 10:30.740
or was so completely hidden by a cap,

10:31.160 --> 10:35.500
that not a shining lock of it ever once gushed into the sunshine.

10:36.660 --> 10:38.920
It was due in part to all these causes,

10:39.300 --> 10:41.280
but still more to something else,

10:41.280 --> 10:44.940
that there seemed to be no longer anything in Hester's face

10:44.940 --> 10:46.720
for love to dwell upon,

10:47.300 --> 10:51.060
nothing in Hester's form, though majestic and statue-like,

10:51.580 --> 10:55.100
that passion would ever dream of clasping in its embrace,

10:55.900 --> 11:00.560
nothing in Hester's bosom to make it ever again the pillow of affection.

11:02.040 --> 11:04.560
Some attribute had departed from her,

11:04.820 --> 11:08.140
the permanence of which had been essential to keep her a woman.

11:09.300 --> 11:11.040
Such is frequently the fate,

11:11.220 --> 11:15.060
and such the stern development of the feminine character and person,

11:15.400 --> 11:16.840
when the woman has encountered,

11:16.920 --> 11:20.580
and lived through, an experience of peculiar severity.

11:22.180 --> 11:24.940
If she be all tenderness, she will die.

11:25.620 --> 11:29.860
If she survive, the tenderness will either be crushed out of her,

11:30.120 --> 11:32.700
or, and the outward semblance is the same,

11:32.700 --> 11:37.800
crushed so deeply into her heart that it can never show itself more.

11:38.560 --> 11:41.060
The latter is perhaps the truest theory.

11:42.100 --> 11:45.200
She who has once been a woman and ceased to be so,

11:45.440 --> 11:47.820
might at any moment become a woman again,

11:48.060 --> 11:51.560
if there were only the magic touch to affect the transformation.

11:52.720 --> 11:57.780
We shall see whether Hester Prynne were ever afterwards so touched and so transfigured.

11:58.840 --> 12:01.700
Much of the marble coldness of Hester's impression

12:01.700 --> 12:05.700
was to be attributed to the circumstance that her life had turned

12:05.700 --> 12:09.660
in a great measure from passion and feeling to thought.

12:10.740 --> 12:11.840
Standing alone in the world,

12:12.280 --> 12:14.700
alone as to any dependence on society,

12:15.120 --> 12:17.700
and with little pearl to be guided and protected,

12:18.400 --> 12:21.000
alone and hopeless of retrieving her position,

12:21.480 --> 12:24.340
even had she not scorned to consider it desirable,

12:25.060 --> 12:28.040
she cast away the fragment of a broken chain.

12:28.640 --> 12:31.700
The world's law was no law for her mind.

12:32.320 --> 12:36.040
It was an age in which the human intellect, newly emancipated,

12:36.900 --> 12:41.560
had taken a more active and a wider range than for many centuries before.

12:42.720 --> 12:45.860
Men of the sword had overthrown nobles and kings.

12:46.860 --> 12:50.280
Men bolder than these had overthrown and rearranged,

12:50.540 --> 12:53.480
not actually, but within the sphere of theory,

12:53.660 --> 12:55.520
which was their most real abode,

12:55.520 --> 12:58.260
the whole system of ancient prejudice,

12:58.740 --> 13:01.320
wherewith was linked much of ancient principle.

13:02.680 --> 13:04.740
Hester Prynne imbibed this spirit.

13:05.420 --> 13:07.500
She assumed a freedom of speculation,

13:07.820 --> 13:10.500
then common enough on the other side of the Atlantic,

13:11.080 --> 13:13.720
but which our forefathers, had they known it,

13:13.980 --> 13:15.900
would have held to be a deadlier crime

13:15.900 --> 13:18.780
than that stigmatized by the scarlet letter.

13:19.720 --> 13:22.440
In her lonesome cottage by the seashore,

13:22.440 --> 13:27.500
thoughts visited her such as dared to enter no other dwelling in New England.

13:27.920 --> 13:32.740
Shadowy guests that would have been as perilous as demons to their entertainer

13:32.740 --> 13:36.000
could they have been seen so much as knocking at her door.

13:37.440 --> 13:40.680
It is remarkable that persons who speculate the most boldly

13:41.300 --> 13:46.940
often conform with the most perfect quietude to the external regulations of society.

13:47.600 --> 13:49.580
The thought suffices them,

13:49.840 --> 13:52.940
without investing itself in the flesh and blood of action.

13:53.620 --> 13:55.900
So it seemed to be with Hester.

13:56.320 --> 13:59.860
Yet had little Pearl never come to her from the spiritual world,

14:00.220 --> 14:02.120
it might have been far otherwise.

14:02.700 --> 14:05.140
Then she might have come down to us in history,

14:05.540 --> 14:07.380
hand in hand with Anne Hutchinson,

14:08.000 --> 14:10.140
as the foundress of her religious sect.

14:10.800 --> 14:14.000
She might, in one of her phases, have been a prophetess.

14:14.000 --> 14:16.900
She might, and not improbably would,

14:17.320 --> 14:20.520
have suffered death from the stern tribunals of the period

14:20.520 --> 14:24.980
for attempting to undermine the foundations of the Puritan establishment.

14:26.200 --> 14:28.200
But in the education of her child,

14:28.560 --> 14:32.520
the mother's enthusiasm of thought had something to wreak itself upon.

14:34.020 --> 14:37.960
Providence in the person of this little girl had assigned to Hester's charge

14:37.960 --> 14:40.160
the German blossom of womanhood,

14:40.160 --> 14:44.020
to be cherished and developed amid a host of difficulties.

14:44.940 --> 14:46.800
Everything was against her.

14:47.160 --> 14:48.620
The world was hostile.

14:49.240 --> 14:52.000
The child's own nature had something wrong in it

14:52.000 --> 14:55.230
which continually betokened that she had been born amiss,

14:56.100 --> 14:58.560
the effluence of her mother's lawless passion,

14:59.160 --> 15:02.820
and often impelled Hester to ask, in bitterness of heart,

15:03.360 --> 15:07.920
whether it were for ill or good that the poor little creature had been born at all.

15:08.960 --> 15:12.500
Indeed, the same dark question often rose into her mind

15:12.500 --> 15:14.940
with reference to the whole race of womanhood.

15:15.660 --> 15:19.620
Was existence worth accepting, even to the happiest among them?

15:20.500 --> 15:23.120
As concerned her own individual existence,

15:23.540 --> 15:25.960
she had long ago decided in the negative

15:25.960 --> 15:28.280
and dismissed the point as settled.

15:29.320 --> 15:34.140
A tendency to speculation, though it may keep woman quiet, as it does man,

15:34.580 --> 15:35.980
yet makes her sad.

15:35.980 --> 15:40.440
She discerns it may be such a hopeless task before her.

15:42.000 --> 15:47.640
As a first step, the whole system of society is to be torn down and built up anew.

15:48.140 --> 15:52.400
Then the very nature of the opposite sex or its long hereditary habit,

15:52.800 --> 15:54.380
which has become like nature,

15:55.120 --> 15:58.960
is to be essentially modified before woman can be allowed to assume

15:58.960 --> 16:01.720
what seems a fair and suitable position.

16:02.520 --> 16:05.720
Finally, all other difficulties being obviated,

16:06.580 --> 16:10.060
woman cannot take advantage of these preliminary reforms

16:10.060 --> 16:14.620
until she herself shall have undergone a still mightier change,

16:14.920 --> 16:19.940
in which perhaps the ethereal essence wherein she has her truest life

16:19.940 --> 16:22.340
will be found to have evaporated.

16:23.640 --> 16:27.720
A woman never overcomes these problems by any exercise of thought.

16:27.720 --> 16:31.220
They are not to be solved, or only in one way.

16:32.080 --> 16:35.300
If her heart chants to come uppermost, they vanish.

16:36.320 --> 16:40.220
Thus Hester Prynne, whose heart had lost its regular and healthy throb,

16:40.700 --> 16:43.960
wandered without a clue in the dark labyrinth of mind,

16:44.480 --> 16:47.780
now turned aside by an insurmountable precipice,

16:48.000 --> 16:50.520
now starting back from a deep chasm.

16:51.460 --> 16:55.220
There was a wild and ghastly scenery all around her,

16:55.220 --> 16:57.520
and a home and comfort nowhere.

16:59.760 --> 17:03.000
At times a fearful doubt strove to possess her soul,

17:03.180 --> 17:06.140
whether it were not better to send Pearl at once to heaven,

17:06.500 --> 17:11.060
and go herself to such futurity as eternal justice should provide.

17:12.160 --> 17:14.920
The scarlet letter had not done its office.

17:16.160 --> 17:19.620
Now, however, her interview with the Reverend Mr Dimmesdale

17:19.620 --> 17:24.000
on the night of his vigil had given her a new theme of reflection,

17:24.000 --> 17:28.460
and held up to her an object that appeared worthy of any exertion

17:28.460 --> 17:30.460
and sacrifice for its attainment.

17:31.740 --> 17:35.720
She had witnessed the intense misery beneath which the minister struggled,

17:36.240 --> 17:39.300
or to speak more accurately, had ceased to struggle.

17:39.980 --> 17:42.780
She saw that he stood on the verge of lunacy,

17:43.200 --> 17:45.800
if he had not already stepped across it.

17:46.120 --> 17:50.200
It was impossible to doubt that whatever painful efficacy

17:50.200 --> 17:53.000
there might be in the secret sting of remorse,

17:53.000 --> 17:56.200
a deadly avenom had been infused into it

17:56.200 --> 17:58.280
by the hand that proffered relief.

17:59.500 --> 18:02.860
A secret enemy had been continually by his side

18:02.860 --> 18:05.560
under the semblance of a friend and helper,

18:06.080 --> 18:09.260
and had availed himself of the opportunities thus afforded

18:09.260 --> 18:13.140
for tampering with the delicate springs of Mr Dimmesdale's nature.

18:14.880 --> 18:18.260
Hester could not but ask herself whether there had not originally

18:18.260 --> 18:22.660
been a defect of truth, courage and loyalty on her own part

18:22.660 --> 18:25.920
in allowing the minister to be thrown into a position

18:25.920 --> 18:28.980
where so much evil was to be foreboded,

18:29.200 --> 18:31.320
and nothing auspicious to be hoped.

18:32.540 --> 18:36.520
Her only justification lay in the fact that she had been able to discern

18:36.520 --> 18:41.840
no method of rescuing him from a blacker ruin than had overwhelmed herself,

18:42.320 --> 18:46.540
except by acquiescing in Roger Chillingworth's scheme of disguise.

18:47.380 --> 18:49.920
Under that impulse she had made her choice,

18:49.920 --> 18:55.080
and had chosen, as it now appeared, the more wretched alternative of the two.

18:56.220 --> 19:00.400
She determined to redeem her error so far as it might yet be possible.

19:01.260 --> 19:03.940
Strengthened by years of hard and solemn trial,

19:04.060 --> 19:08.000
she felt herself no longer so inadequate to cope with Roger Chillingworth

19:08.000 --> 19:12.120
as on that night, abased by sin and half-maddened by the ignominy

19:12.120 --> 19:16.160
that was still new when they had talked together in the prison chamber.

19:16.780 --> 19:20.120
She had climbed her way since then to a higher point.

19:21.100 --> 19:24.840
The old man, on the other hand, had brought himself nearer to her level,

19:25.060 --> 19:29.160
or perhaps below it, by the revenge which he had stooped for.

19:30.100 --> 19:33.900
In fine Hester Prynne resolved to meet her former husband

19:33.900 --> 19:38.220
and do what might be in her power for the rescue of the victim

19:38.220 --> 19:41.200
on whom he had so evidently set his grip.

19:42.660 --> 19:44.640
The occasion was not long to seek.

19:44.640 --> 19:49.440
One afternoon, walking with Pearl in a retired part of the peninsula,

19:50.000 --> 19:55.800
she beheld the old physician with a basket on one arm and a staff in the other hand,

19:56.100 --> 20:01.280
stooping along the ground in quest of roots and herbs to concoct his medicine withal.

